sub_title: Professor of Emerging and Zoonotic Viruses at Wageningen University and Research
summary: Senior scientist at the Wageningen Bioveterinary Research and Special Professor of Emerging and Zoonotic Viruses at Wageningen University and Research (WUR), The Netherlands. Research areas: 1. Emerging Viruses, 2. Zoonotic Viruses, 3. Foodborne Viruses, 4. Global One Health. Actively involved in ERRAZE@WUR programme, in which health disciplines work together on pandemic preparedness. Coordinator of the EPIZONE European Research Group on Epizootic Animal Diseases Research. Chair of the Scientific Committee of the International Research Consortium for Animal Health. Diplomate of the European College of Veterinary Microbiology.
